Detailed Description

A JoinRule is used to specify a criterion on how to join data items. See also: StandardJoinRule.

Member Enumeration Documentation

enum JoinRule::RelationType
 

The RelationType determines the maximal number of joins from the frst_item to the snd_item parameter in ExecuteRule.

Enumerator:
Injective  Each fst_item has at maximum one join to the snd_items.
Surjective  Each snd_item has at maximum one join to the fst_items.
Bijective  Each fst_item has at maximum one join to a snd_items and vice versa.
Cartesian  Each fst_item can have a join to each of the snd_items.
